# Canonical line endings for the whole site, declared once.
#
# Everything here is either machine-written (update.json by scripts/release.mjs,
# revocations.json by scripts/generate-revocation-list.mjs, both LF) or edited by
# hand on Windows, and all of it is served over HTTP where line endings mean
# nothing. Naming only those two files left every other file to core.autocrlf's
# per-file guess, so the working copy drifted apart - index.html ended up CRLF
# while invite.html and the site-*.js files stayed LF - and any commit touching
# an LF file warned "LF will be replaced by CRLF".
#
# Declaring LF for everything removes the guess: repo and working copy agree on
# every machine, and that warning cannot come back. Nothing stored changes -
# autocrlf already normalised the blobs to LF on the way in; this only fixes
# what git writes back out on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Screenshots are binary. Keep the text filters away from them entirely.
*.png binary
*.webp binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
